message: Initial commit.
Updates documentation.
Removes commented method in HTMLParser.
Fixes issue with attributes with different casing for name did not match.
#7: Starts adding unit tests and fixes bug with CustomEvent not being defined.
#7: Adds unit tests for html-parser and location.
Starts refactoring they way options are sent into HTML element renderer.
Reverts start of refactoring as it should be on a separate branch.
#9: Adds support for requestAnimationFrame and cancelAnimationFrame.
#45@major: Lerna is used for managing multiple packages within a single repo. Support for React and Angular. Full support for querySelector() and querySelectorAll().
#45@major: Lerna is used for managing multiple packages within a single repo. Support for React and Angular. Full support for querySelector() and querySelectorAll().
#45@major: Lerna is used for managing multiple packages within a single repo. Support for React and Angular. Full support for querySelector() and querySelectorAll().
#56@patch: Fixes the release process.
#70@patch: Fixes release notes build.

#248@minor: Adds a new package called "global-registrator" to the Happy DOM mono-repo. The package contains a utility that registers Happy DOM globally, which makes it possible to use Happy DOM for testing in a Node environment.

#276@patch: Due to a bug in Lerna, npm-shrinkwrap.json was published to NPM, even though it was referenced in .npmignore. The bug caused both dev and normal dependencies to be installed in node_modules as a sub-directory. This resulted in Happy DOM to take much more space than necessary.
#275@trivial: Fixes lint issues.
#281@minor: Adds support for Jest v27.0.0 to @happy-dom/jest-environment.

#425@minor: Updates all dependencies to fix security vulnerabilities. Fixes issue with objects and functions not having the same constructor as window.Object and window.Function in a virtual environment.
#425@trivial: Downgrades Chalk, as it requires ESM.
#425@trivial: Downgrades Chalk, as it requires ESM.
#534@trivial: Fixes failing compile and test in global-registrator.
#697@patch: Upgrade jest dependencies to 29.4.0.

Migrated scripts to turborepo
